    "long_instructions": "### Add a sound in real-time\r\n\r\nPart of live coding is preparation. Every performance has some element of planning and some element of improvisation. \r\n\r\n**Do this:** \r\n- Planning: Find at least three new sounds that you can layer into your backtrack. Think about when you want to add or remove each of those sounds. \r\n- Improvisation: As you listen, challenge yourself to break from the plan by adding that sound earlier or later than expected. Take mental notes on what felt good and you'll skip next time.\r\n\r\n*NOTE: Quickly close the sound picker dropdown menu so the sound preview doesn't overlap with your song.*",
